<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-42-0998 </DOCNO><TEXT>In vivo glucose utilization was measured in the suprachiasmatic nuclei(SCN) of Golden hamsters using the {sup 14}C-labeled deoxyglucose technique.A circadian rhythm of SCN metabolic activity could be measured in thisspecies, but only during pentobarbital sodium anesthesia when the surroundingbackground activity of adjacent hypothalamus was suppressed. Both theSCN's metabolic oscillation and its time-keeping ability are resistantto general anesthesia.</TEXT></DOC>